| Massachusetts Likely To Approve OOXML                              |
|   from the et-tu-deval dept.                                       |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday July 03, @08:08 (Microsoft)         |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/03/0255201     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Ian Lamont writes "The IT department of the state government of
[1]Massachusetts has designated Microsoft's Office Open XML as an open
document format, along with ODF, plain text, and HTML. It's only a draft
policy, but it sets the stage for the format being given an official
stamp of approval by state authorities — and weakens earlier
Massachusetts support for the Open Document Format. Microsoft got a big
boost at the end of 2006 when Ecma approved OOXML, and again this spring
when [2]pro-ODF legislation was being defeated or watered down in six
states."

