interesting. 'The admission hurts SAP's reputation in the battle with
Larry Ellison's Oracle in the $56 billion market for software that
manages tasks such as payroll. The rivalry between SAP and Oracle
escalated when Oracle filed its March 22 lawsuit claiming SAP workers
hacked into a Web site and stole software codes on a grand scale.'"

