| Software Speeds Response To Road Accidents                         |
|   from the fluid-like-no-other dept.                               |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday July 03, @15:35 (Software)          |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/03/1916218      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]coondoggie alerts us to research out of Ohio State University that
could help authorities [1]respond to car accidents more quickly and ease
traffic back-ups at lower cost, particularly in rural areas. The software
improves the efficiency of communications from in-road vehicle detection
loops to transportation engineers monitoring conditions in order to
improve traffic flow. Faster response to accidents and traffic jams could
have huge payoffs: a 2002 study estimated that traffic jams cost the
average city almost a billion dollars a year.

